snippet.textDisplay: Mary's bath, after Mary the Jewess, a third century apothecary and philosopher, wildly held to be one of the world's first alchemists and chemists, she is credited with the first description of the technique/apparatus and potentially it's invention. Many other early pieces of equipment and devices for distillation and extraction as well as general methodology, are though to have be first catalogued by her and possibly be of her own invention, quite a few of which are still used to this very day in modern science labs, distilleries and pharmacies, some with very little modification to their original designs.
